Vice President Kamala Harris delivered a commencement address at the Navy-Marine Corps Memorial Stadium in Annapolis, Maryland. She congratulated the graduating class of 2021 and highlighted the challenges and opportunities they will face in the rapidly changing world. She emphasized the importance of cybersecurity and defending against modern threats, as well as addressing climate change as a national security issue. Harris praised the military's contributions during the COVID-19 pandemic and encouraged the graduates to hold onto their ideals and fight for democracy. She reminded them that they are part of a team and urged them to remember the words "We, the people" from the Constitution. Harris also paid tribute to Senator John McCain and Admiral Chuck Larson, emphasizing the spirit of being "in it together." She expressed confidence in the graduates and the nation's faith in them as they take the oath to defend and serve.